{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5023", "repo": "rails", "body": "I guess a setting is a reasonable compromise, although I'm loath to add further complexity to Rails. And really, if you're dealing with SSL but haven't tested it locally through a browser, then I'd be a little worried.\r\n\r\nAnd yes, dealing with SSL in development isn't quite so simple, but that's what the gem I've built addresses - and I'm sure others have their own work-arounds - such as what you've written in your second example.", "_id": {"$oid": "52381dbebd3543c15100e610"}, "issue_id": 5023, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4033287", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5023#issuecomment-4033287", "updated_at": "2012-02-18T10:39:48Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat", "login": "pat", "gravatar_id": "29f82ebe1801087f04de6aaae92e19ea", "html_url": "https://github.com/pat", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/29f82ebe1801087f04de6aaae92e19ea?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F217f5e7754c92d28fc6835d42f43548d.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 4183, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/pat/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-02-18T10:39:48Z", "id": 4033287, "owner": "rails"}
